events.name: Intro to GCPDFW Meetup / Google Cloud Platform Overview
events.description:
What
This is it, our first meet up!  During our first session, we will do a brief introduction to the mission of our group and will have a functional overview of the key areas, tools, and services of Google Cloud Platform.  We're going to be joined by a few members of the Google team who will help out with the overview and I'm sure they'll be happy to answer questions.  Following the intros, we'd like to do a brief open discussion about where members would like to focus in future sessions (topics, speakers, activities, etc.).

We'd like to get started as close to 5:30pm as possible, but understand that travel could delay some folks from being there so we'll kick off once we have a decent turnout.

Our sponsors will graciously be picking up the tab for drinks (yes that means beer!) and food.  Due to venue constraints, we'll only be able to take the first 50 who RSVP.  Based on attendance and interest, we will look into larger venues for future meet ups.

Where
Flying Saucer Draft Emporium (Addison)
14999 Montfort Dr, Dallas, TX

When
Tuesday, July 11th, 2017 @ 5:30pm CT

Questions
If you have any questions, don't hesitate to message me on Meetup!

events.name: GCP Console - Managing Projects and Deploying an Application on GCP
events.description:
Join us for this session to learn about using the GCP Project Console.  We'll walk through the ins and outs of the console, setting up to work with GCP on your local machine, and how to deploy a project.  We'll cover tips and best practices for configuration and setup along the way.

Doors will open shortly after 5:00pm and we'll kick-off once we have a majority of the confirmed attendees or at 5:45pm, whichever comes first.  We'll try to reserve a bit of time for general forum/Q&A following the presentation as well.

Food and drinks will be provided by our sponsor Precocity, LLC.

Exciting Update: after a bit of work and coordination our friends from Google have been able to get us into their offices in Addison for our meeting!  Special thanks to them and I know I'm looking forward to it just for the location!  We will post any updates or additional details about how to get into the office as they come.

events.name: Machine Learning and Big Data on Google Cloud Platform
events.description:
Machine Learning on GCP: Jobin Thomas, Chief Data Scientist for Superior Data Science LLC will walk us through using Machine Learning on GCP. He has been experimenting with using GCP ML on his projects and will be able to share what it takes to get started using it on your own.

Big Data on GCP: Venu (Vidya) Vidyashankar, Enterprise Data Architect for Heartland Payments Systems, will be presenting an overview of Big Data tools on GCP from a development and architecture perspective. His company is currently on GCP and he will be able to share his experiences using the tools professionally.

We look forward to seeing you all there on the 12th!

events.name: GCP in Production: Evolution of Microservices (talk and Q&A)
events.description:
For our next meet up, we wanted to do something a bit different from our prior tech talks.  This time we're going to have a current Google Cloud customer to present and discuss their experience building microservices on GCP.  Randall Lee has graciously offered to share the Home Depot team's experience and how their services have evolved.  We should have some time for questions as well following the presentation if you're curious about production-ready GCP microservices.

If your organization is determining whether to make the jump, this is going to be a must attend session!

Note: We will be meeting in a different location that is still to be determined for this month as our normal spot is unavailable.  As such, for now the RSVP slots will be lower than normal until we confirm how much space we'll have, but we have a fallback location if necessary.  Watch here for more info on location.

Update:  Location has been settled and we're going to be meeting in the Addison TreeHouse!  I've update the location on the meeting details and I'll be upping the number of attendee openings we have.
events.how_to_find_us: Come to the 2nd floor of building 5, if you have trouble finding the place ask for the Treehouse.

events.name: GCP DFW 2018 Kick-off and Networking Social
events.description:
• What we'll do
Hello all and happy 2018! We've got some exciting news to share about the group and we've been waiting for some final details to be able to do so. We have been invited to be a part of Google's Cloud Development group community!!! This is a great opportunity for us to both have a greater community to reach out to and will give us access to resources for our meetups.

To kick the year off, we'd like to have a social event to discuss where we are and where we're going in 2018. There will be a few changes that will need to happen which are still being finalized, but one thing we know for sure is that we need to bring in more people to help at the organizational level. So, if you're interested in helping organize and run the group, definitely join us on Thursday!

Here are the topics we'll cover:
- What the changes mean for the group
- Meetup leadership team (additions and formalization)
- Topic for meetings this year
- Q&A

We hope you can join us and if not, we'll share a rundown of everything after the meetup. Our current plan is to schedule another meetup in the next two weeks for our first official content session of 2018.

• What to bring

• Important to know

events.description:

Want to get started on the Google Cloud, but don't know where to begin?

Join us for our Cloud Study Jam! Together we'll work through three Google Cloud Platform Essentials labs, then you will get free access to the next quest so you can finish this series of labs at home to get a Google-hosted badge for your online profile. events.name: Workflow Orchestration on Google Cloud Using Apache Airflow
events.description:
ABOUT THE TALK:
Join us for a technical walkthrough on setting up, configuring, using Apache Airflow to orchestrate complex workflows. We'll do an end-to-end walkthrough and share information on best practices and use cases for Airflow as a workflow orchestration tool and you will be able to access a sample project on GitHub afterwards to walk through an example yourself.

Google Cloud now offers a managed version of Airflow called Cloud Composer that we will briefly touch on during this meeting, but will go into in deeper detail in a follow-up session.

ABOUT AIRFLOW:
Apache Airflow is an open-source tool for orchestrating complex computational workflows and data processing pipelines.

WHAT TO BRING:
Nothing required, but you may want to be able to take notes and you're also welcome to bring a laptop to follow along in the repo as we go.

Join us for a special presentation from Looker and OrderMyGear on how you can use BigQuery and Looker on Google Cloud to perform analytics at scale. Looker will provide a technical presentation on their ecosystem and how it fits in with a Google Cloud data and analytics implementations and OrderMyGear will give real customer experiences on moving to Google Cloud and using BigQuery and Looker to run analytics for their business.

AGENDA:

About Looker:
Looker is a business intelligence software and big data analytics platform that helps you explore, analyze and share real-time business analytics easily.

- Looker can leverage BigQuery unique functionality, running directly in the database and whereby querying 250 Gb in under 5 seconds
- Looker has pre-built blocks and applications for BigQuery Transfer Service, which helps makes sense of all of your data instantly - great application for all your marketing data
- Looker’s unique in-database architecture connects directly to Cloud SQL, allowing customers to build a data platform to expose deep insights from transactional and operational data within minutes
- Instantly leverage value from the numerous Looker Blocks for Google Cloud

About OrderMyGear
Our platform empowers thousands of businesses along the supply chain of group apparel sales — from team dealers and decorators to brands and distributors — to create a better selling experience, grow their business, and allow them to focus on what they do best.

events.name: Serverless Data Processing & Analytics on Google Cloud Platform
events.description:
Join us for a technical walkthrough on setting up ingestion pipelines for both batch and streaming data loading data directly into Google BigQuery. We’ll cover the specifics on how to create Dataflow jobs designed to reduce the complexity, pain, and engineering time of onboarding a new dataset to BigQuery. We’ll also demonstrate how to gain insights from the data quickly using BigQuery showing concepts such as schema creation and query and cost analysis.

This presentation will cover a variety of Google Cloud technologies including:
- Dataflow
- BigQuery
- PubSub
- Cloud Shell
- GCS

This is part 2 of our 3 part series on building an end-to-end data pipeline in Google Cloud. You don't have to have been to the prior meetings to get the benefits of this session.

events.name: Cloud ML: 3 Easy Ways to Get Started (AutoML, SQL, Keras) and How to Choose One
events.description:
[DESCRIPTION]:
Machine Learning continues to become more democratized -- the tools and libraries are easier to use, and there are a variety of different abstractions now available. Whether you are a developer who does mostly Java, a data analyst who works in SQL, or a data scientist who works in Python/R, you can now solve machine learning problems at a pretty high-level. We will walk through solving the same text classification problem using Auto ML, using SQL, and using Keras on Google Cloud Platform. Then, we will talk about the tradeoffs of each approach, and how a business might choose between these approaches (i.e., which team would do what).

[SPEAKER BIO]:
Lak is currently a Tech Lead for Big Data and Machine Learning Professional Services on Google Cloud Platform. He is the author of Data Science on GCP (O'Reilly) and Machine Learning on GCP (Coursera). His mission is to democratize machine learning so that it can be done by anyone anywhere using Google's amazing infrastructure (i.e., without deep knowledge of statistics or programming or ownership of lots of hardware).
